caption: Coffee does not taste that good to begin with.  Add to that bad service and an inability to grasp simple concept of first-in-first-out when preparing drinks.  2 visits, months apart and same poor experience.  Walked out without coffee rather that try to enlighten staff on their shortfalls.  They actually make Starbucks look good.  Ha.
The coffee is always empty between 7-8 am, and customer service is deplorable.

Super nice staff. Same good food like Pret elsewhere in the world.
Good food, excellent coffee, and super staff!!  This is the place to go!
Very cool healthy place to eat has a variety of affordable snacks and food
(Translated by Google) Price!  (Original) Pret!
(Translated by Google) Pret a Manger is the best healthy food gastro food in the world.  (Original) Pret a Manger é o melhor gastro food de comida saudável do mundo.
Always solid
All the staff here are super friendly and I will keep coming back. Quick & easy. I like the soups and simple sandwiches.
The food was bad, staff were nice .
The bread is delicious, the lattes fine. However, staffs are not quite welcoming. And a little pricy.
Excellent service at this location. The Staff is so warm and welcoming I adore them.   (:)
Good sandwich shop come grab and go

Excellent as is the norm for Pret everywhere. But there remains an annoying tendency to play loud synth-laden,auto-tuned, modern club dance music as if all the customers are under age 30. Take it down a notch, mix it up a little and try to appeal to the customers’ taste, not just staff. It can be high energy, if need be (& from almost any decade)...reliably excellent food, though& keep up the great work.

Used to be a lot better but still great! Back in the day, the baristas would punch my card all the time and joke with me, sometimes even give me the coffee for free when I was visibly stressed out since I'm a nearby student (my school is around the corner). They don't do that anymore which is a shame, I definitely go less now and recommend it less now, but not terrible. Still good prices for coffee in the area
Im glad there's one at 30th Street Station.
Good food great staff.
Extremely helpful and capable staff at this location. Thanks Dolores and crew!
(Translated by Google) They do not know how to make a coffee with milk.  (Original) No saben hacer un café con leche.
Coffee here is really good but their pastries are better!
I like the salads and the already prepared food. You never have to wait long.

Being a millennial I love Pret. I'm pretty sure they drainedd it to draw us in haha. The way they do things just makes sense to me. There were calorie counts on all the food so I could make an informed choice, and the pricing was reasonable. So much better than dunks or starbucks. This one was clean and well kept. I enjoyed my reasonable breakfast.
A half sandwich is great for an afternoon snack.

This place used to be good: you could pick a fresh, crisp baguette with some fine ingredients and make it a delicious lunch. Now it seems the bread is stale and soggy, the sandwiches look like day-old and the prices are off the charts. A tuna baglette and an avocado juice came to $16 - I felt stupid to be honest. Pret-a-Manger can do better?

This was the Pret. Here, or maybe near, I became a Google explorer.  I really like Pret as a company.  They might even be an essential thread in the quilt of a modern, civil, city.  I wish we had a few in Baltimore.  Pret is also one of those places where employees are trained not to accept tips.  No one should not to be able to accept a tip for excellent service.  Now that the service industry has been turned upside down in DC by referendum, Pret should allow Laron, who who over filled my flat white and immediately made me a new one, to receive my gratitude for his excellent service. Thank you.

They try to seem special by their fresh and organic signs but the menu shown doesn’t show much for teas, coffee and pastries are not even shown.  The Pret app I downloaded seems limited but nowhere do I see rewards.  I really wanted to like this place but wasn’t even offered a receipt until I asked.  The table I sat at had a lot of crumbs on it and overall looking at the floor it wasn’t clean.  $3.29 for a small raisin croissant which was very good but felt way overpriced for the size.
Typical Prett with all the goodies
i lovet hat they donate the left overs to the homeless.

Outstanding array of heathy, delicious entrees and sides. Loved the roasted cauliflower, mushroom Pate, falafel salad with a mustard vinaigrette dressing. Clean dining area. Friendly, helpful service. Highly recommended.

This branch is my favorite place for lunch or coffee. I ask anyone who wants to meet me for coffee after work there. The lentil soup is the best and I love the focus on healthy eating. But what makes it really the best is the staff. Anwar and Mustafa have worked over a year at that location and are the best! I have watched them interact with the customers and they are consistently friendly and upbeat. It's a.cheerful environment for a a anyone needing a break from a long day at the office
There is much positive energy in this location and Anwar is one of the most attentive persons there. He is always smiling and high energy than anyone else in the food places around .
I love this place!
Nice vegetarian soups. Seating not very comfortable but ok for quick lunch.
Great muffins
Rock hard bread on my sandwich.

username: Lev Agranovich, EA MSA CFC PA CDFA

caption: I'll admit it. I am a Pret A Manger fan. Yes, it's a chain, but it's consistent and their food is so good (and more affordable). This location is downtown DC near Franklin Square Park and a tab smaller, but still has all the offerings you'd expect in a Pret A Manger- a fresh fruit stand, delicious wraps and sandwiches for lunch, an array of warm pastries, and a coffee bar. There's indoor and outdoor seating to boot too! If you go in the morning, I recommend eating the 400 calories and getting a warm chocolate hazelnut croissant. It's amazing!
The food was great for a sandwich shop, very fresh and high quality.   Got a pastry for desert that was very tasty also.   My wife is very picky about ingredients and she looked it.
I love this Pret! Awesome service and great team working behind the counter. Happy to have in the neighborhood !!! :)
Good affordable breakfast
Wonderful!

What's not to love?  Clean, well stocked, friendly staff, fast service.... It meets all of the Pret A Manger requirements.... It's in the financial district of town, (which also happens to have quite a few hotels) steps from the Metro.  Quick-casual... Ready to eat... Pre-packaged, but good... Tried the Moroccan lentil soup today (comes with tasty petite baguette) and was in heaven.  Vegan and vegetarian friendly options.  And, won't break the bank to boot.  Yes Yes... Do try!

Pret offers a wide selection of food in the go that satisfies my hunger on any given day.  The staff at this location is very friendly and gets through the line quickly.  The food is always stocked and warm or cold depending on the requirements of the item.  Highly recommend if you are looking for lunch on the go, but don't forget about breakfast, that's good too!
Great place very good fast food
Easy place to grab a quick bite
Great selection, great tasting food, and excellent customer service. Can't wait to return again!!
(Translated by Google) Tasty and healthy food. Nice to find such places in America.  (Original) Вкусная и здоровая еда. Приятно находить такие места в  Америке.
Great breakfast and seating outside.
Good take-and-go sandwiches and great iced coffee. Good location with indoor and outside seating. Some people say it's on the pricey side for fast food.
I love this place. Very delicious light food I always grab some when I'm in the area.
Love it!

Cashier short changed me $15 and tried to make me, the customer, look like the a$$h0l3. Kept calm and finally got my correct change back after management got involved. No apologies from the manager or chasier afterwards. A *possible* operation going on here.
Really like this place. Food is simple, not heavy, but tasty at the same time. They did a great job for the price. You are not going to leave stuffed feeling disgusting.
Expensive coffee, clean dining
A solid choice for healthier fair in the neighborhood.
Small portions, no extra condiments, too many rules, make it clear you are marketing target.

This was my go-to place during lunch. The staff is always nice. They have alot of fresh items, but you must go there by 11:30 if you want to get the freshest sandwiches. The avocado goes bad here alot, so beware. Inspect before you buy.
Little pricey, but sooooooo delicious!!
(Translated by Google) Good place for lunch. Fast service and the food is rich.  (Original) Buen lugar para almorzar.  Servicio rápido y la comida es rica.
Food presented well, clean store, prices I'm line with DC pricing. Staff could have been more personable or at a minimum smile.
Good
Very clean and hipster but cool spot. Good iced coffee
My first time Experience was awesome with Great Customer Service by Ms. Taylor very outstanding!!!! :) very clean great latte thank you ! Definitely coming back to the store again!

This place does a pretty good job of feeling authentic, even though it is a chain. Visiting in the morning, you'll find yourself tempted by the sweet, buttery smell of freshly-baked pastries wafting through the air. I get that they are in a hurry during rush times, but the lady who rang me up today was in too much of a rush to even look at us customers, and one second after the purchase, she was calling the next patron up. For beverages, I do like their cold-pressed raw juices, and they offer a variety of flavors, like carrot, beet,  greens, etc.

This location has great food just like all the other ones, but the dining area has fruit fly problems.  I don't like bugs trying to land on me or my food.  I eat here once or twice a week despite the fruit flies.

My go to here is the Balsamic Chicken & Avocado sandwich. I try not to come here too often, because I feel really guilty for coming here since the sandwiches look like something I could/should be making myself at home. However, Pret A Manger never disappoints me. In addition to the chicken & avocado sandwich, I also really love the snacks that are available at the check-out counter. I usually purchase a bag of popcorn or some type of bar to go with my lunch.
Nice sandwiches with healthy ingredients, nice place to hang out, have a nice day.
A sure thing for something sweet.   Friendly staff.
Good food, fast/friendly service, reasonable prices, and free wifi with some plug available. Enough said.
